column2: radi allahu (islamic word, cannot be translated)

muslims believe that the quran refers to what was most proper that refers to the way that is most correct, and fairest. allah says: "verily this qur'an refers to what was most appropriate and brings happy news to believers who do good deeds to reward awaits them." general characteristics of this era was nomartivizam, which is discussed in the attitudes of trade, interest rates, fair price, etc., which is related to the values ​​and goals, as opposed to positive economics, which is set of synthesized  knowledge of what exists in practice - life.
